WEBVTT

00:01.966 --> 00:05.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the day's other news,
world powers are jousting over
how to handle North Korea's

00:05.266 --> 00:08.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
test of an intercontinental
ballistic missile.

00:08.000 --> 00:12.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The president of China,
Pyongyang's closest ally,
called for restraint.

00:12.900 --> 00:17.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In Europe earlier today,
President Trump says
he still hopes that
Beijing can help resolve

00:19.733 --> 00:21.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the North Koreans'
tensions, but said the U.S.
has a range of options.

00:21.700 --> 00:23.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

00:23.200 --> 00:25.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
TRUMP: I don't like to talk
about what I have planned.

00:25.133 --> 00:30.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But I have some pretty
severe things that we
are thinking about.

00:31.333 --> 00:32.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That does not mean we
are going to do them.

00:32.133 --> 00:34.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I don't draw red lines.

00:34.666 --> 00:38.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's a shame that they're
behaving this way, but
they are behaving in
a very, very dangerous

00:40.900 --> 00:44.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
manner and something will
have to be done about it.

00:44.300 --> 00:46.433 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

00:46.433 --> 00:48.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Meanwhile, there's
word that it was Russia that
blocked the U.N. Security

00:48.566 --> 00:53.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Council's approval of
a statement strongly
condemning that launch.

00:53.300 --> 00:58.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The Trump administration
has renewed its offer
to cooperate with Russia
over the Syria conflict.

01:00.900 --> 01:04.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In a statement last night,
Secretary of State Rex
Tillerson said the U.S.
is open to coordinating

01:05.166 --> 01:07.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
on no fly-zones in Syria.

01:07.900 --> 01:12.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Later, State Department
spokeswoman Heather Nauert said
the broader American strategy

01:12.300 --> 01:13.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
remains the same.

01:13.300 --> 01:15.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

01:15.400 --> 01:17.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HEATHER NAUERT, STATE
DEPARTMENT SPOKESWOMAN:
If our two countries
can establish stability

01:17.933 --> 01:20.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on the ground, we believe
that will lay a foundation
for progress on the
political settlement

01:20.500 --> 01:22.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of Syria's future.

01:22.600 --> 01:26.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The policy has not changed,
some of the words and some of
the phrasing may have changed

01:28.633 --> 01:31.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at this point, but overall,
it's just one of a series of
options that the United States

01:31.600 --> 01:32.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
will now consider.

01:32.600 --> 01:34.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

01:34.633 --> 01:37.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: For his part, Russia's
foreign minister, Sergey Lavrov,
asked for more information

01:37.200 --> 01:42.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on the proposal, but said
cooperation is, quote, a
step in the right direction.

01:44.166 --> 01:47.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A survey commissioned by the
State Department shows diplomats
are frustrated and confused

01:48.433 --> 01:50.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
by the Trump administration.

01:50.433 --> 01:54.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"The Wall Street Journal"
first reported on the document,
which was released to State

01:54.033 --> 01:56.166 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Department employees yesterday.

01:56.166 --> 02:01.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It comes as the president seeks
drastic cuts to diplomatic
and development funding.

02:03.000 --> 02:06.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Separately, the State Department
is saying the U.S. refugee
admissions program won't

02:07.666 --> 02:09.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
be suspended until next week.

02:09.766 --> 02:14.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
After the Supreme Court
upheld part of the Trump
administration's travel
ban, re-settlement

02:16.066 --> 02:19.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
agencies were told to
schedule refugee arrivals
only through today.

02:19.300 --> 02:24.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But it's been announced that
they can now continue until July
12th, when refugee admissions

02:25.500 --> 02:27.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
are expected to hit
their cap of 50,000.

02:27.933 --> 02:32.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The government ethics director
who has prodded the Trump
administration over conflicts of

02:33.666 --> 02:35.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
interest is resigning.

02:35.366 --> 02:40.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Walter Shaub is stepping
down months before his
term was set to expire.

02:40.000 --> 02:44.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In a statement on Twitter, he
said: It has become clear to
me that we need improvements

02:44.933 --> 02:47.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to the existing ethics program.

02:47.366 --> 02:52.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This follows the resignation
of a top Justice Department
official over ethics concerns.

02:54.366 --> 02:58.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Democratic attorneys general
in 18 states and the District
of Columbia are suing Education

03:00.400 --> 03:05.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Secretary Betsy DeVos,
over her delay of rules
on for-profit colleges.

03:07.066 --> 03:10.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The lawsuit demands the
implementation of the
rules created under the
Obama administration.

03:12.933 --> 03:16.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They're meant to cancel the
student-loan debt of people
defrauded by those schools.

03:18.133 --> 03:21.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Illinois House of
Representatives has voted to
over-ride the governor's veto of

03:22.300 --> 03:24.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a budget package.

03:24.366 --> 03:28.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It means that Illinois
will have its first annual
spending plan since 2015.

03:30.333 --> 03:33.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That is the longest
state fiscal crisis since
the Great Depression.

03:33.133 --> 03:38.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lawmakers voted 71 to 42 to
approve the $36 billion budget
plan, which is funded with

03:39.600 --> 03:43.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
a $5 billion income
tax increase.

03:43.433 --> 03:48.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On Wall Street today, stocks
had their biggest drop in more
than six weeks, amid signs that

03:49.166 --> 03:50.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
hiring has slowed.

03:50.800 --> 03:55.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The Dow Jones Industrial
Average lost 158 points
to close at 21320.

03:56.966 --> 04:01.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Nasdaq fell 61 points, and
the S&amp;P 500 dropped almost 23.
